textBox.richText: Alli had a bunch of runs she wanted to bag today: Belle, the Cirque, the Chutes, and Brians. WP got a bunch of snow yesterday during the day (7”), and with Pano closed most of the day, Belle was definitely top of the target list. Met up with James; headed that way, until we saw the Cirque was open. HAD to hike that...came down west headwall. Did a couple laps through Left Hand and Belle after that...Alli went off to lunch, while we did another lap through Belle and Eagle. Met up with her after, and nabbed Brian’s...then headed over and did the Chutes. Finished off the day with Tophers....good snow, good day!!!
